 BY ANDREW EKEJIUBA Former Super Eagles dare-devil striker Emmanuel Emenike has reportedly built a hospital in his hometown, in Imo State. The news has been disclosed via a video posted on Instagram as reported by OmaSports. Emenike and his friends have been spotted driving inside the building, the source confirms. “So many footballers use their money to f**k supermodels, but you made sure you brought your wealth back home to support our people, congrats Nwokeoma on your luxury hospital. 2021 we move…” was the caption under the video. Emenike won the 2013 AFCON with Nigeria and made 37 appearances with the Super Eagles.  